The paper deals with the problem of learning the structure of an Ising model from i.i.d. samples, which is a problem of interest in machine learning and statistics. The paper proposes a new algorithm for learning Ising models on arbitrary bounded-degree graphs, which is a problem in the field of machine learning and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves analyzing the computational complexity of the proposed algorithm, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper proposes a new structural property of Ising models, which could be of interest to researchers in the field of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
